  "root_text": {
    "sn38.10:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 38.10 ",
    "sn38.10:0.2": "1. Jambukhādakavagga ",
    "sn38.10:0.3": "Taṇhāpañhāsutta ",
    "sn38.10:1.1": "“‘Taṇhā, taṇhā’ti, āvuso sāriputta, vuccati. ",
    "sn38.10:1.2": "Katamā nu kho, āvuso, taṇhā”ti? ",
    "sn38.10:1.3": "“Tisso imā, āvuso, taṇhā. ",
    "sn38.10:1.4": "Kāmataṇhā, bhavataṇhā, vibhavataṇhā—",
    "sn38.10:1.5": "imā kho, āvuso, tisso taṇhā”ti. ",
    "sn38.10:1.6": "“Atthi panāvuso, maggo atthi paṭipadā, etāsaṁ taṇhānaṁ pahānāyā”ti? ",
    "sn38.10:1.7": "“Atthi kho, āvuso, maggo atthi paṭipadā, etāsaṁ taṇhānaṁ pahānāyā”ti. ",
    "sn38.10:1.8": "“Katamo panāvuso, maggo katamā paṭipadā, etāsaṁ taṇhānaṁ pahānāyā”ti? ",
    "sn38.10:1.9": "“Ayameva kho, āvuso, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, etāsaṁ taṇhānaṁ pahānāya, seyyathidaṁ—",
    "sn38.10:1.10": "sammādiṭṭhi …pe… sammāsamādhi. ",
    "sn38.10:1.11": "Ayaṁ kho, āvuso, maggo ayaṁ paṭipadā, etāsaṁ taṇhānaṁ pahānāyā”ti. ",
    "sn38.10:1.12": "“Bhaddako, āvuso, maggo bhaddikā paṭipadā, etāsaṁ taṇhānaṁ pahānāya. ",
    "sn38.10:1.13": "Alañca panāvuso sāriputta, appamādāyā”ti. ",
    "sn38.10:1.14": "Dasamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn38.10:0.1": "Linked Discourses 38.10 ",
    "sn38.10:0.2": "1. With Jambukhādaka ",
    "sn38.10:0.3": "A Question About Craving ",
    "sn38.10:1.1": "“Reverend Sāriputta, they speak of this thing called ‘craving’. ",
    "sn38.10:1.2": "What is craving?” ",
    "sn38.10:1.3": "“Reverend, there are these three cravings. ",
    "sn38.10:1.4": "Craving for sensual pleasures, craving for existence, and craving for nonexistence. ",
    "sn38.10:1.5": "These are the three cravings.” ",
    "sn38.10:1.6": "“But, reverend, is there a path and a practice for completely understanding these cravings?” ",
    "sn38.10:1.7": "“There is.” … ",
